BEAT THE SUN WITH SUNSCREEN



The saying that too much of a good thing can turn into a bad thing comes to mind when talking of shielding ourselves from the sun. While it is true that life on earth thrives because of the sun, there are rays of sunlight that can cause irreparable damage to our skin. Even people of ancient civilizations had figured this out so different regions found their own solutions. For instance, the Greeks applied olive oil to their skin. Early Egyptians mixed the extract of rice, jasmine and lupine plants as protection from the sun and some of these ingredients are found in sunscreen formulations today too.

One of the most effective ingredients that can be found in even the best sunscreen is zinc oxide paste which is said to have been used since well over a thousand years. It was not until as recently as 1928 that the first synthetic sunscreen lotion made an appearance in skin care. Keep reading to know why you should start using one that will keep you looking younger for longer.

REASONS TO NEVER SKIP ON SUNSCREEN


Beauticians have been talking about using this product for a long time for several reasons, here are a few of them below.

  1. UV Rays

    With the continuous depleting of the ozone layer, there is no string defence against the harsh rays of the sun. One of the most detrimental rays of the sun are its UV rays which can cause acceleration of skin disorders. So be sure to select the best sunscreen lotion for your body and apply it according to the instructions, before or after your body lotion or foundation.

  2. Skin Cancer

    While many might consider protecting their bodies from the sun for beauty reasons, there are many health benefits to the practice too. You will be happy to know that using sun protection also prevents skin cancer. So, every time you cleanse your face with face wash and tone it before stepping out, you are potentially saving your skin in the long run in terms of health. If you are a guy reading this, it should motivate you to start using a sunscreen for men regularly, if you don’t do so already.

  3. Premature Aging

    Everyone loves having skin that is supple and blemishes free, as they age. Sunscreen will let you have that by reducing your chances of developing ageing signs by 24%, below the age of 55. Remember to re-apply the product to your face every couple of hours, because sunscreen for oily skin should have a lighter formulation.

CHOOSING THE ONE FOR YOU


You can buy any sunscreen you want on Myntra, we have put together some information to help you choose wisely.

Types of Sunscreen

The first kind is mineral or a physical sunscreen, which was referred to as ‘sunblock’ until 2011. They are formulations that act as a barrier between your skin and the sun. The predominant ingredients include zinc oxide or titanium dioxide, which reflect the rays.

The second is the chemical variety and is generally considered to be the more effective kind. This is because instead of sitting on the top layer, they are absorbed by the skin. They convert radiation into heat and simply release it through the skin.

How to Pick

The best sunscreen for oily skin would be one with a water-based formula. For those with normal skin, any sunscreen would be compatible. As a rule of thumb, physical barriers should be applied last and the chemical kind must be given time to be absorbed by freshly cleansed skin. Chemical sunscreens must be reapplied often so carrying yours around is a great idea.

GO SHOPPING ONLINE


At Myntra, we have stocked up on all your favourite sunscreens, whether it is BB cream, CC cream brands or more. Shop on your couch and pick from an incredible range of clothes, shoes as well as accessories of every kind at discounted prices, with free shipping and order tracking too. Be prepared to have yourself a slice of the retail pie!


  • DO I NEED TO WEAR SUNSCREEN EVERY DAY?



    • Yes, it is necessary to apply sunscreen every day to prevent your skin from getting damaged. Applying or spraying a good amount of sunscreen could help prevent sunburns and other skin-related conditions.  Sunscreen primarily helps minimise the effects of ultraviolet (UV) radiation and prevents possible damage at the cellular level. For best protection, apply a fluid ounce of SPF 15 sunscreen across the body every two hours. 



  • WHEN TO APPLY SUNSCREEN?



    • Listed below is a glimpse into when sunscreen proves to be the most beneficial: 
  • Apply sunscreen 30 minutes prior from stepping out in the sun. This timeframe helps your skin absorb the sunscreen without washing it off as you sweat.
  • It is essential to apply sunscreen if you wear hats, protective clothing, or work outdoors.
  • Reapplying sunscreen after strenuous exercises or swimming activities is a must as moisture from excessive sweating can wash off the cream.
    • Note: Do not apply moisturizer, lotion, or any makeup products on the top of the sunscreen, as it can dilute the solution and impact its efficiency.



  • WHAT IS SPF IN SUNSCREEN?



    • SPF is a measure to identify the ability of sunscreens to protect skin from harmful UV rays. SPF protects the skin from reddening and surface burns and reduces the chances of ageing, wrinkles, and cancer.  Sunscreen SPF are divided into three categories - 15 (mild), 15-30 (moderate), and 30+ (high protection). For example, if a normal skin turns red within a minute’s exposure to the sun, apply SPF 15 sunscreen longer. Whereas, if it takes 10 minutes for the skin to get burnt, consider applying SPF 30 sunscreen.
